A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing the Civil Air Patrol for their service to the citizens of Georgia; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Civil Air Patrol was founded on December 1, 1941, as an organization of
4 volunteers meant to assist the United States military in national defense by performing aerial
5 coastal patrols and emergency services within the continental United States; and
6 WHEREAS, in 1943, the capabilities of this new volunteer organization were recognized as
7 vital to national defense, and by Presidential Executive Order, the Civil Air Patrol was
8 assigned to the War Department and subsequently designated by Congress on May 26, 1948,
9 as the official auxiliary to the United States Air Force to perform three distinct missions:
10 emergency services, aerospace education, and cadet programs; and
11 WHEREAS, Civil Air Patrol's association with the United States Air Force in performing
12 these "Missions for America" as part of the United States Air Force's Total Force; and
13 WHEREAS, the Georgia Wing of Civil Air Patrol consists of almost 2,000 volunteer
14 members in 44 squadrons and six groups located throughout this state; and
