15 WHEREAS, Georgia Wing members received national recognition in 2021 by receiving the
16 Crisis Service Award for their efforts to support Georgia's communities during the
17 COVID-19 pandemic; and
18 WHEREAS, Georgia Wing members, as an intricate component of our national defense,
19 volunteer their services, time, and resources to actively support Civil Air Patrol by
20 conducting missions in homeland security, disaster relief, and emergency services, search
21 and rescue, counter drug, aerospace education, and cadet programs, heavily supporting
22 hurricane relief efforts for Helene and Milton by providing FEMA and GEMA with
23 thousands of aerial images and conducting "Sundown Patrols" in South Georgia; and
24 WHEREAS, the estimated value of the Georgia Wing members' volunteer hours in 2024 was
25 in excess of $7.6 million; and
26 WHEREAS, these "flying minutemen" of the Civil Air Patrol have, since its inception,
27 consistently provided this state with invaluable emergency services, serving America's
28 communities, saving lives, and shaping futures.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body recognize the selfless contributions that the volunteers of the Civil
31 Air Patrol have made to the State of Georgia.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
34 Georgia Wing of the Civil Air Patrol.
